OL,3,COverstretched NHS putting cancer
OL,4,Cpatients at risk, ombudsman warns
OL,6,FIt comes as Parliamentary and Health
OL,7,FService Ombudsman (PHSO) figures
OL,8,Frevealed 1,019 investigations relating
OL,9,Fto cancer were carried out between
OL,10,FApril 2020 and December 2023. Of the
OL,11,Fcomplaints, 185 cases were upheld or
OL,12,Fpartly upheld.
OL,14,FThe most common issues involved the
OL,15,Flikes of treatment delays and
OL,16,Fmisdiagnosis, while the majority of
OL,17,Finvestigations involved patients with
OL,18,Flung cancer, breast cancer and
OL,19,Fcolorectal cancer.
